titleStmt.title: An entry from the Journals of Hensley Henson

sourceDesc.bibl: Edited from the manuscripts in the custody of Durham Cathedral Library.

p.hi: I continued my reading of McKecknie: walked with Logic: called on old John Wilson, who is perceptibly weaker, and not likely to rise from his couch: paid £150 into my banking account: & wrote divers letters. Received a pleasant letter from Olaf.
